title._content: Court Street from Union Street, Keene, NH

description._content: TITLE Court Street from Union Street, Keene, NH CREATOR SUBJECT Streets - NH - Keene Houses - NH - Keene Elms - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of Court Street taken from Union Street looking south, located in Keene New Hampshire. In 1785 a road was laid out from the Keene Meetinghouse to Surry and beyond. After completion of the new meetinghouse in 1788, the county accepted the old building to use as a court house and moved it to a place about in line with the center of Court Street as it is today. In 1796, a road was laid out to pass west of the new court house. The straight course and width of Court Street was established in 1808. The road was part of the Third N.H. Turnpike and after that was given up in 1822, the selectmen laid out the road over the same course.
